article.headline: Princeton 59, Cornell 46
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Princeton moved one step closer to the Ivy League championship by beating Cornell 59-46 on Saturday for its sixth straight win. At 10-1, the Tigers' magic number for clinching the title dropped to two with three games to play. Brown is 9-3 and Penn is 8-3 in league play. Cornell slipped to 11-14 and 6-6 in league. KaRon Barnes, averaging almost 21 points coming in, topped the Big Red with 14. Andre Logan led five players in double figures for Princeton (17-7) with 12 points and 14 rebounds, while Scott Greenman also had 12 points. Will Venable and reserve Luke Owings had 11 each. Judson Wallace's streak of scoring 20 or more points ended at five games as he also finished with 11.
